    "body": "I return from the depths of the backlog.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIf `'keywordprg'` begins with `:`, `3K` turns the count into an Ex range. Commands that don't support that then fail. Vim passes the count as the first arg (see #19436, vim/vim#10745).\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nPass `[count]` as the first arg for `'keywordprg'`.\r\n\r\nAll credit to #19600, which did exactly this but got closed for being out-of-date and missing a test.\r\n\r\nfix https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19436",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-12T12:44:56Z",
